hor_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "The following code fails to compile:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nfn main() {\r\n    let mut foo = std::collections::BinaryHeap::new();\r\n\r\n    let Some(mut top) = foo.peek_mut() else { return };\r\n    *top = 1u32;\r\n    println!(\"{top:?}\");\r\n    foo.pop();\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nGiving an error of: \r\n\r\n```\r\nerror[[E0499]](https://doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/error_codes/E0499.html): cannot borrow `foo` as mutable more than once at a time\r\n --> src/main.rs:7:5\r\n  |\r\n4 |     let Some(mut top) = foo.peek_mut() else { return };\r\n  |                         -------------- first mutable borrow occurs here\r\n...\r\n7 |     foo.pop();\r\n  |     ^^^^^^^^^ second mutable borrow occurs here\r\n8 | }\r\n  | - first borrow might be used here, when `top` is dropped and runs the `Drop` code for type `PeekMut`\r\n\r\nFor more information about this error, try `rustc --explain E0499`.\r\n```\r\n\r\nAs it's not used, I can easily just insert `drop(top);` before  `foo.pop();`, but I think that the compiler should be doing that in this case.\r\n\r\nTested on:\r\nrust stable 1.70 edition 2021\r\nrust nightly 1.72 2023-06-07 a97c36dd2e6f711949fc edition 2021\r\n\r\n", "closed_by": {"login": "rottedfrog", "id": 8600702, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjg2MDA3MDI=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/8600702?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/rottedfrog", "html_url": "https://github.com/rottedfrog", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rottedfrog/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rottedfrog/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rottedfrog/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rottedfrog/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rottedfrog/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rottedfrog/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/user